देषासुस्थिराबुद्धिर्मृत्युलोभादुपस्थिता ।भयान्नशक्तस्त्वांमोक्तुमनिरस्तस्संयुगे रक्षसानांचसर्वेषामात्मनश्चवधेनहि ।","trans":"\"This thought has come to him only to cause him death. Because of impending death, he is very steady in his mind. This Ravana will not be able to liberate you before his death and of the Rakshasas.\"","words":[{"d":"तत्","m":"to him"},{"d":"मृत्युलोभात्","m":"cause death"},{"d":"एषा","m":"this"},{"d":"सुस्थिरा","m":"very steady"},{"d":"बुद्धिः","m":"thought"},{"d":"उपस्थिता","m":"impending"},{"d":"तु","m":"to you"},{"d":"संयुगे","m":"in combat"},{"d":"सर्वेषाम्","m":"every one"},{"d":"राक्षसानाम्","m":"of the Rakshasas"},{"d":"आत्मनश्च","m":"himself also"},{"d":"वधेन","m":"by death"},{"d":"अनिरन्तः","m":"undetermined"},{"d":"भयात्","m":"out of fear"},{"d":"त्वाम्","m":"you"},{"d":"मोक्तुम्","m":"to liberate"},{"d":"नशक्तः","m":"not able."}]},{"v":26,"dev":"निहत्यरावणंसङ् ख्येसर्वथानिशितैश्शरैः प्रतिनेष्यतिरामस्त्वामयोध्यामसितेक्षणे: ।","trans":"\"Rama will kill Ravana in war with his sharp arrows and take you back to Ayodhya, O darkeyed lady!\"","words":[{"d":"असितेक्षणे","m":"darkeyed"},{"d":"रामः","m":"Rama"},{"d":"सङ् ख्ये","m":"war"},{"d":"निशितैः","m":"sharp रावणम् Ravana"},{"d":"निहत्य","m":"killing"},{"d":"त्वाम्","m":"you"},{"d":"अयोध्याम्","m":"Ayodhya"},{"d":"प्रतिनेष्यति","m":"will take back."}]},{"v":27,"dev":"एतस्मिन्नन्तरेशब्दोभेरीशङ्खसमाकुलः श्रुतोवानरसैन्यानांकम्पयन् धरणीतलम् ।","trans":"In the meantime (while Saarana was telling Sita) the sounds of drums and conchs combined with the clamour of Vanara troops was heard and it was as though the surface of the earth was shaking.","words":[{"d":"एतस्मिन् अन्तरे","m":"in the meantime from inside"},{"d":"वानरसैन्यानाम्","m":"Vanara troops"},{"d":"भेरीशङ्खसमाकुलः","m":"sounds of drums and conches"},{"d":"धरणीतलम्","m":"earth surface"},{"d":"कम्पयन्","m":"shaking"},{"d":"शब्दः","m":"sound"},{"d":"श्रुतोवै","m":"was heard."}]},{"v":28,"dev":"श्रुत्वातुतद्वानरसैन्यशब्दंलङ्कागताराक्षसराजभृत्याः ।नष्टौजसोदैन्यरीतचेष्टाःश्रेयोनपश्यन्तिनृपस्यदोषैः","trans":"On hearing the sounds of Vanara troops, the Rakshasas present in Lanka became dull, overcome by depression, thinking that because of Ravana's mistakes they could not see any good prospects for them. ।। इत्यार्षेवाल्मीकीयेश्रीमद्रामायणेआदिकाव्येयुद्धकाण्डेचतुस्त्रिंशस्सर्गः ।। This is the end of the thirty fourth sarga of Yuddha Kanda of the first epic the holy Ramayana composed by Valmiki.","words":[{"d":"तम्","m":"those"},{"d":"वानरसैन्यशब्दम्","m":"sound of Vanara troops"},{"d":"श्रुत्वा","m":"on hearing"},{"d":"लङ्कागताः","m":"present in Lanka"},{"d":"राक्षसराजभृत्याः","m":"by the mistakes of the king of Rakshasas"},{"d":"नष्टौजसः","m":"became dull"},{"d":"दैन्यरीतचेष्टाः","m":"overcome by depression"},{"d":"नृपस्य","m":"Ravana's"},{"d":"दोषात्","m":"mistakes"},{"d":"श्रेयः","m":"prospect"},{"d":"नपश्यन्ति","m":"could not see."}]}]}